claim: Marie Curie conducted pioneering research on space.
premise_source_doc_sentence: Marie Skłodowska Curie  (  -LSB- ˈkjʊri , _ kjʊˈriː -RSB- -LSB- kyʁi -RSB- ; -LSB- kʲiˈri -RSB- ; 7 November 18674 July 1934  )  , born Maria Salomea Skłodowska  (  -LSB- ˈmarja salɔˈmɛa skwɔˈdɔfska -RSB-  )  , was a Polish and naturalized-French physicist and chemist who conducted pioneering research on radioactivity .
